site_desc:
Right bank of Wolf Creek Glacier, St. Elias Range, between Base Camp, 1941 and mouth of Wolf Creek.  
[On sheet of original notes attached to card]:  3 miles east (downstream) of base camp on Wolf Creek glacier St. Elias Range, Yukon Territory, Canada.
site_notes:
2"-11/2' high. North-facing slope back of lateral moraine.
[From sheet of original notes]: North facing hill slope back of lateral moraine of Wolf Creek glacier. Tundra vegetation and other willows associated weathered, slumped Pleistocene till. Elevation about 5000' +/- ?
                                                        Low (2"-11/2 ') stragly[sic] bush, usually in open and by itself. Does not form clumps or thickets. Leaves when fresh have rather shiny apple green colour and bark is brown to green.

Tundra, 2' high.
